    "body": "Problem:\n\nMouse shape does not change when hovering over resizable elements.\n\nSolution:\n\nUpdate the mode when hovering over resizable elements (statusbar and vsep) and set the mshape property. Respond to mode changes in the TUI by updating the mouse shape via the [OSC 22 escape sequence](https://sw.kovidgoyal.net/kitty/pointer-shapes/#pointer-shape-names)\nreference: https://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/21458\n\nTODO:\n- [x] vsep mouse cursor doesn't show up on bufload\n  - need to do some unintuitive actions like opening a terminal buffer\n  - the `mshape` is uninitialized memory\n  - `tui_mode_info_set` is called but cursor_shapes is not updated\n  - classic use after free\n- [x] change mouse cursor on horizontal separators\n- [ ] support `mouseshape` option\n- [ ] put current cursor on a stack on nvim enter\n  - how to handle terminal buffers setting the cursor?\n- [ ] query for mouse shape support to determine if should enable\n- [ ] confirm if mshape backwards incompatible(?) change on `mshape` for `mode_info_set` is valid\n  - it's a bit awkward otherwise... we could maybe add a mapping between ints and names as an option or add a new field altogether\n- [ ] respect `used_for` to not change the cursor shape for mouse only modes\n  - needed so that the cursor shape is not unexpected when in a mouse only mode\n- [x] keep resize cursor _while_ resizing (horizontal flickers, vertical just converts back to default)\n  - needed to `setmouse()` after `jump_to_mouse()`\n- [ ] get confirmation on the path forward for other elements like links\n- [ ] disable if `mousemoveevent` is `false`",
